│ ### 5. Conclusion                                                                          │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root cause of the assertion failure is a known and deliberate difference in how the    │
│ legacy and VPlan-based cost models handle `trunc to i1` instructions used in control flow. │
│ The legacy model considers them free, while the VPlan model assigns a cost. The fix is to  │
│ update the `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` utility function, which is part of the  │
│ assertion check, to be aware of this specific discrepancy. By ignoring `trunc to i1`       │
│ instructions in this check, we acknowledge the costing difference and prevent the          │
│ assertion from incorrectly flagging a valid divergence between the two models.             │
